  "texts": [
    "The 96-well plate was then incubated at 50 °C for 60 min, after which the Gibson products were placed on ice.",
    "These Gibson products could then either be directly used for transformation or stored at -20 °C for later use.",
    "To each well of the previously described Gibson assembly plate was added 5 μL of T7 Express Competent E. coli.",
    "The cell solutions were allowed to incubate on ice for 20 min, after which they were heat-shocked at 42 °C for 10 s in a water bath.",
    "The cells were then recovered with the addition of 100 μL of LB."
  ],
